measurementvalue: We acknowledge that this research was conducted on the unceded and unsurrendered traditional territories of the Mi'kmaq, Passamaquoddy, Wabanaki (Bay of Fundy ecodistrict); Mi’kmaq, Wabanaki (Magdalen Shallows, Scotian Shelf); Métis peoples (Churchill Estuary-Hudson Bay); and the Inuit homelands of Inuit Nunangat including: Nunatsiavut (NL-Labrador Shelves), Nunavik (Southern Hudson Strait), and Nunavut (Baffin Bay/Davis Strait, North Baffin Fjords). Arctic data collections were funded by ArcticNet, Polar Knowledge Canada, DFO (Aquatic Invasive Species Monitoring Program, Strategic Program for Ecosystem-Based Research and Advice [SPERA], Ocean Protection Plan [OPP] Coastal Environmental Baseline Program, Arctic Science Funds, GRDI), Nunavut Wildlife Management Board, Nunavik Marine Region Wildlife Board, and World Wildlife Funds to KH and ALR. Field accommodations and/or logistic support during Arctic field campaigns were provided by Churchill Northern Studies Centre, Glencore-Raglan, Baffinland Iron and Vale Mines, NRCan (Polar Continental Shelf program), Nunatsiavut Government, Environment and Climate Change Canada, and Government of Nunavut MV Nuliajuk.
